  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>The phrase <code>I'm on it</code> is a common informal expression used to assure someone that you are actively working on a task or issue that has been addressed or requested. It's a casual way of saying that one is taking responsibility or action.</p>\n<p>For example, if someone asks, <code>Can you please send me the report?</code> and you respond with <code>I'm on it</code>, it means you are either starting or already in the process of doing it.</p>\n</section>",
